			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>An Algorithm for Layout Preservation in Refactoring Transformations</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MaartjedeJonge.html">Maartje de Jonge</a>, <a href="../profile/EelcoVisser.html">Eelco Visser</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_3">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_3</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagM">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It proposes an algorithm for source-to-source refactoring while preserving concrete layout/formatting.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagL">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> Refactorings are framed as program transformations with specific correctness constraints.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagL">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> Refactoring is a maintenance activity aimed at improving existing code without changing behavior.
</li></ul></li></ul>
